7 : Innovating in the kitchen by experimenting with international cuisines can introduce a variety of healthy and flavorful ingredients into your diet, making healthy eating a delightful experience.
8 : Focusing on portion control is as important as food quality; eating in moderation ensures you get the necessary nutrients without excess calories, aiding in effective weight management.
9 : Embracing a plant-based diet, rich in legumes, nuts, seeds, and whole grains, can provide substantial health benefits, including lowered risk of chronic diseases and improved digestion and metabolism.
